    Use templated index for smoke tests. (#250)
    
    * Use templated index for smoke tests.
    * Update changelog.
    Rework ES mappings (#242)
    
    * Rework mappings
    
    Add static mappings for parsed fields. Rework mappings. Use properties
    for app and platform index names. Fix some fields parsing
    (@shipper.priority).
    
    * Fix haproxy.* mappings, geoip.* mappings. Delete @cf.origin and *.cf_ignored_app fields (these fields have constant values).
    
    * Rename "APP/PROC/WEB" to just "APP" for simplicity.
    
    * Rework fields @source.index, .job_index and .vm
    
    App logs and platform logs from syslog release pass `job_index` field which is string bosh instance id. So we parse this field and store it as `@source.job_index`.
    Platform logs from metron agent pass `index` field which is numeric instance number. We store this field as `@source.index`. Additionally in this case, we set `@source.vm` field calculated as `job`/`index` (similar to how Logsearch sets it for Nats logs).
    
    Change parsing rules, tests and mappings accordingly.
    
    * Add mappings for new rtr fields
    
    * Update documentation for mappings
    Added Changelog

    https://concourse.altoros.com/ is not working

    Add "exclude app from getting logs in ELK" feature description
    
    Describe how to opt-out apps of getting their logs in ELK using F2S_DISABLE_LOGGING env variable processed by firehose-to-syslog.

    Adds a feature to skip authorization (#272)
    Cookie passphrase (#263)
    
    * Optionally set session cookie encryption passphrase.
    * Expose session key for cf-kibana.
    * Validate session key length.
    src/kibana-cf_authentication Use the auth endpoint for logout
    
    From login server API https://github.com/cloudfoundry/uaa/blob/master/docs/login/Login-APIs.md#login-server-apis
    src/kibana-cf_authentication added Kibana 5.0.0 support
    Use the auth endpoint for auth, and the token endpoint for tokens (#233)
    
    Using the token endpoint for authorization is incorrect and will break the session-based-redirect flow for UAA users delegating authentication to external IDPs
    Use token_endpoint for authorization_uri and logout_uri
    Fix use_https correct processing
    Add "redirect" parameter when calling UAA /logout.do during Kibana logout.
    
    Redirect to Kibana /login after logout. Implemented using "redirect" parameter of UAA "/logout.do" endpoint. NOTE, that to work normally, redirects after logout should be enabled in UAA - https://github.com/cloudfoundry/uaa/blob/3.9.3/uaa/src/main/resources/login.yml#L38-L45.
    Also add useful comments to kibana-cf_authentication plugin.
    Fix infinite redirect loop when uaa-oauth cookie > 4K.
    Allow insecure Kibana connection
    Extend plugin with User page containing Logout button
    Fields rework
    
    Make the same platform and app fields consistent, add useful fields.
    
    1. Sync. app basic fields (@source etc.) with platform fields (so that both indices have the same basic fields); Platform: set @source.origin field to 'system'/'cf'.
    2. Store app specific json cf_ fields to @cf;
    3. Set @type to specific values for platform logs (uaa, haproxy or vcap);
    4. Set parsed_json_data_field_name to handle name of parsed json field. We store app parsed json to field named of @type (e.g. rtr, app etc.). And we store vcap message parsed json and app msg parsed json to field named of @source.component value;
    5. App parsing: store event_type to @type, source_type to @source.type.
    6. Rename parsed_json_data to parsed_json_field.
    7. Add field @index_type to store platform/app value.
    8. Update ES mappings and Kibana objects accordingly.
    Filter search endpoint by org and space for non-privileged users.
    Change Kibana session expiration
    
    Set Kibana session expiration to a reasonable value of 12h. Make this value configurable.

    which actually included also es-mappings and kibana-saved-objects, we now
    split it and have three separate jobs (and packages accordingly):

    First implementation of new add-on structure.  #14
    Move gorouter parsing to separate file
    Write up-to-date documentation
    Add parsing of different app events
    
    1. Set [@source][type] from dictionary for all events; additionally override it with source_event for LogMessage events.
    2. Change parsing of LogMessage, ContainerMetric to make generic solution for all event types. Add parsing of missing event types: Error, ValueMetric, CounterEvent, HttpStart, HttpStop, HttpStartStop.
    3. Rename snippets to make their names reflect the events they parse.
    Fields rework
    
    Make the same platform and app fields consistent, add useful fields.
    
    1. Sync. app basic fields (@source etc.) with platform fields (so that both indices have the same basic fields); Platform: set @source.origin field to 'system'/'cf'.
    2. Store app specific json cf_ fields to @cf;
    3. Set @type to specific values for platform logs (uaa, haproxy or vcap);
    4. Set parsed_json_data_field_name to handle name of parsed json field. We store app parsed json to field named of @type (e.g. rtr, app etc.). And we store vcap message parsed json and app msg parsed json to field named of @source.component value;
    5. App parsing: store event_type to @type, source_type to @source.type.
    6. Rename parsed_json_data to parsed_json_field.
    7. Add field @index_type to store platform/app value.
    8. Update ES mappings and Kibana objects accordingly.
    General refactoring
    
    1) refactoring in snippets (optimize filters, fix formatting, comments)
    2) refactoring in UTs (change checks to get fail-fast for not-related fields, fix describe messages, improve checks)
    3) add haproxy fail grok unit test case
    4) rename vcap fail json tag
    Rename snippets
    
    Rename snippets to bring more clarity into their functional purpose.
    Fields rework
    
    1. Remove _logstash_input field (we don't need it because we have @input field containing value of log input)
    2. Do not rename tags to @tags. This is incorrect to rename tags because logsearch-boshrelease also sets some tags after logsearch-for-cloudfoundry filters processed.
    3. Simplified if checks in snippets
    4. Reworked @type field
    5. Get rid of unparsed index (default index is platform)
    6. Update tests
    Split firehose snippet to several & Add UTs for app filters & refactoring in tests
    
    1) Split firehose snippet to several app* snippets for easier maintenance.
    2) Add UTs for app filters.
    3) Minor refactoring in existing tests.
    Platform filters decomposition
    
    Move common platform logs parsing to a separate snippet - platform.conf.
    
    New snippet platform.conf combines deleted undefined.conf and platform filtering common logic.
    So platform.conf snippet now parses logs using general CF logs format (metron_agent format) + sets common fields. Other platform snippets are applied afterwards.
    Fields refactoring
    
    Add @input field. Remove syslog_pid; Remove [@job][host].
    Set [@source][host] where it was missing.
    Set @message for uaa.
    Check JSON format more strictly (vcap).
    Rename grok fail tag (undefined);
    Remove square brackets where we access simple fields (e.g. use @level instead of [@level]).
    Unify events timestamp by setting 'date' from metron_agent timestamp
    
    Do not set event 'date' from specific logs timestamp fields anymore. Set it from metron_agent timestamp instead (to have time consistency between logs of different sources).
    Fix firehose parsing to set 'date' from <JSON>.timestamp field instead of <JSON>.time because in fact 'timestamp' is right field that contains timestamp from metron_agent (see https://github.com/cloudfoundry-community/firehose-to-syslog/issues/79 for description of time fields in firehose JSON).
    Filters decomposition & additional processing
    
    Filters decomosition:
    Move common 'init' logic to 'setup' script and call it from default.conf.erb before all snippets. Similarly move all common 'cleanup' logic to teardown.conf and call it after all snippets.
    
    Additional procesing:
    1) Add processing of undefined CF logs in undefined.conf snippet (parsing of those logs that are not parsed by any of existing special snippets like uaa, vcap etc.).
    2) Make teardown.conf set @level and @source.component fields from corresponding syslog* fields if they haven't been set in snippets (we need to have at least some value for these fields cause they are significant some).
    Filters refactoring & rework:
    1) Rewrite firehose and uaa snippets to follow common scripts structure. Minor changes in comments.
    2) Uaa, firehose: add @shipper.* fields; do not use old 'remove' option in mutate (replaced with 'remove_field'); lowercase UAA fields (UAA.* -> uaa.*).
    3) Firehose: replace unicode Null character (\0000) with "" and drop empty logs; fixed convertion of HTTP status code to @level.
    4) Common fields changes: uppercase @level field; rename field tags -> @tags.
    Add parsing rules for CF components (vcap) logs.
    Add parsing rules for haproxy
    Use different indices names for application logs and CF logs. (#103)
    
    * Use different indices names for application logs and CF logs. Store index name in [@metadata][index] field.
    
    * Fix @type field name.
    remove uneeded parsing rules

    Store parsed json to a field with name of @source.component
    
    Different vcap components have different JSON messages, but could contain JSON fields with the same name and different type. This causes Logstash warning and lose of data. So we store parsed JSON to a field named like @source.component so that different components do not intersect in naming of JSON fields.

    Add missing fields to @source from syslog_sd_params
    Handle RFC 5424 syslog format for CF platform logs
    
    The latest syslog-release project introduced a new Syslog log format which is
    based on RFC 5424 [1]. This format is automatically parsed by the Logstash
    filters defined in [2] therefore the grok filters will fail in platform.conf.
    
    We check for syslog_sd_id first and make sure the common fields and tags are set.
    
    [1] https://github.com/cloudfoundry/syslog-release/blob/e58e88281429f0bac1313994db447fce22b29106/jobs/syslog_forwarder/templates/rsyslog.conf.erb#L54
    [2] https://github.com/cloudfoundry-community/logsearch-boshrelease/blob/9c0376bfd403cc63df058a30e6e27e4f0b41c889/src/logsearch-config/src/logstash-filters/snippets/syslog_standard.conf#L3
    Rework ES mappings (#242)
    
    * Rework mappings
    
    Add static mappings for parsed fields. Rework mappings. Use properties
    for app and platform index names. Fix some fields parsing
    (@shipper.priority).
    
    * Fix haproxy.* mappings, geoip.* mappings. Delete @cf.origin and *.cf_ignored_app fields (these fields have constant values).
    
    * Rename "APP/PROC/WEB" to just "APP" for simplicity.
    
    * Rework fields @source.index, .job_index and .vm
    
    App logs and platform logs from syslog release pass `job_index` field which is string bosh instance id. So we parse this field and store it as `@source.job_index`.
    Platform logs from metron agent pass `index` field which is numeric instance number. We store this field as `@source.index`. Additionally in this case, we set `@source.vm` field calculated as `job`/`index` (similar to how Logsearch sets it for Nats logs).
    
    Change parsing rules, tests and mappings accordingly.
    
    * Add mappings for new rtr fields
    
    * Update documentation for mappings
    Rename `@source.instance` to `@source.job_index` (string guid), cease @source.name field
    
    https://github.com/cloudfoundry-community/logsearch-for-cloudfoundry/issues/217 (a change for job_index)
    Because `Index` field passed from Loggregator (doppler) was changed from uint instance number to guid instance ID, and firefox-to-syslog renamed `index` to `job_index`, the following changes were done in parsing:
    1. `@source.instance` renamed to `@source.job_index`. It's datatype changed from int to string - so no more converting to int is necessary.
    2. Because `source.job_index` is no more a short index of a job instance, but its bosh ID, we cease `@source.name` field (calculated as job+index before).
    3. Update Uindices and Kibana saved objects accordingly. Update UTs.
    Support for cloudfoundry/syslog-release log messages
    
    Fix for https://github.com/cloudfoundry-community/logsearch-for-cloudfoundry/issues/204.
    Fix parsing tests. Add tests for new parsing rules.
    Fields rework
    
    Make the same platform and app fields consistent, add useful fields.
    
    1. Sync. app basic fields (@source etc.) with platform fields (so that both indices have the same basic fields); Platform: set @source.origin field to 'system'/'cf'.
    2. Store app specific json cf_ fields to @cf;
    3. Set @type to specific values for platform logs (uaa, haproxy or vcap);
    4. Set parsed_json_data_field_name to handle name of parsed json field. We store app parsed json to field named of @type (e.g. rtr, app etc.). And we store vcap message parsed json and app msg parsed json to field named of @source.component value;
    5. App parsing: store event_type to @type, source_type to @source.type.
    6. Rename parsed_json_data to parsed_json_field.
    7. Add field @index_type to store platform/app value.
    8. Update ES mappings and Kibana objects accordingly.
    Fields rework
    
    1. Remove _logstash_input field (we don't need it because we have @input field containing value of log input)
    2. Do not rename tags to @tags. This is incorrect to rename tags because logsearch-boshrelease also sets some tags after logsearch-for-cloudfoundry filters processed.
    3. Simplified if checks in snippets
    4. Reworked @type field
    5. Get rid of unparsed index (default index is platform)
    6. Update tests
    Firehose parsing: parse new fields
    
    Recent version of firehose-to-syslog passes new fields in json message: deployment, ip, job. Add parsing rules for these fields. Update tests accordingly.
    Split firehose snippet to several & Add UTs for app filters & refactoring in tests
    
    1) Split firehose snippet to several app* snippets for easier maintenance.
    2) Add UTs for app filters.
    3) Minor refactoring in existing tests.
    Filters: Add support of integration tests & Add first integration tests & Refactoring of common fields
    
    1) Add support of integration tests. Integration tests run as part of all tests run and also can be started separately by executing bin/itest.
    2) Add first integration tests (app and platform cases checking common fields).
    3) Move parsing of common fields from snippets to setup.conf script. Snippets can override common fields with specific values if necessary.
    4) Minor refactoring & comments.
    General filters refactoring
    
    Refactoring in 'replace' filter (use up-to-date syntax).
    General filters refactoring.
    Platform filters decomposition
    
    Move common platform logs parsing to a separate snippet - platform.conf.
    
    New snippet platform.conf combines deleted undefined.conf and platform filtering common logic.
    So platform.conf snippet now parses logs using general CF logs format (metron_agent format) + sets common fields. Other platform snippets are applied afterwards.
    Add parsing of different app events
    
    1. Set [@source][type] from dictionary for all events; additionally override it with source_event for LogMessage events.
    2. Change parsing of LogMessage, ContainerMetric to make generic solution for all event types. Add parsing of missing event types: Error, ValueMetric, CounterEvent, HttpStart, HttpStop, HttpStartStop.
    3. Rename snippets to make their names reflect the events they parse.
    Fix parsing tests. Add tests for new parsing rules.
    Add parsing of different app events
    
    1. Set [@source][type] from dictionary for all events; additionally override it with source_event for LogMessage events.
    2. Change parsing of LogMessage, ContainerMetric to make generic solution for all event types. Add parsing of missing event types: Error, ValueMetric, CounterEvent, HttpStart, HttpStop, HttpStartStop.
    3. Rename snippets to make their names reflect the events they parse.
    Get rid of HttpStart, HttpStop events processing
    
    Recently, dropsonde protocol removed HttpStart and HttpStop events,
    leaving HttpStartStop only (https://github.com/cloudfoundry/dropsonde-protocol/commit/3dd1473786cf6acdcc55e2206a58f08ad02f29ca). Even though current version of firehose-to-syslog is still uses these events processing, current versions of CloudFoundry don't operate these events, because they use latest dropsonde protocol. So we can get rid of these events in Logsearch-for-cloudfoundry to simplify processing.
    Change parsing rules after recent fields fixes in firehose-to-syslog 2.0.0
    Fix parsing tests. Add tests for new parsing rules.
    Add parsing of different app events
    
    1. Set [@source][type] from dictionary for all events; additionally override it with source_event for LogMessage events.
    2. Change parsing of LogMessage, ContainerMetric to make generic solution for all event types. Add parsing of missing event types: Error, ValueMetric, CounterEvent, HttpStart, HttpStop, HttpStartStop.
    3. Rename snippets to make their names reflect the events they parse.
    Change parsing rules after recent fields fixes in firehose-to-syslog 2.0.0

    Update RTR log parsing rules
    
    - CF-Deployment v12.27.0 changed the format and fields for the gorouter.
    - Added gorouter_time_ms
    - Also now supports additional headers logged.
    Add a logmessage_rtr config for new gorouter_time and app_time fields (#337)
    
    These fields were introduced in routing-release 0.196.0 https://github.com/cloudfoundry/routing-release/releases/tag/0.196.0 which forms part of cf-deployment v12.17.0 https://github.com/cloudfoundry/cf-deployment/releases/tag/v12.17.0
    Fix router log parsing when `disable_log_source_ip = true` and fix routing API log parsing (#316)
    
    * fix router log parsing when disable_log_source_ip = true
    * allow app_index to be '-' when parsing router logs
    Response status code mapping to log level (#317)
    
    5xx - ERROR
    4xx - WARN
    others - INFO
    Add [rtr][response_time_ms] without using the ruby filter (#287)
    
    We want to use a 3rd party ELK stack where there ruby filter plugin is not
    enabled for security reasons. This commit adds the response_time_ms using gsub.
    The value is truncated at three digits (instead of rounding).
    Updates the precision of response_time_ms (#245)
    
    * Updates the precision of response_time_ms to 3 decimal places for app-logmessage-rtr
    * Fix failing test suite

    Rework ES mappings (#242)
    
    * Rework mappings
    
    Add static mappings for parsed fields. Rework mappings. Use properties
    for app and platform index names. Fix some fields parsing
    (@shipper.priority).
    
    * Fix haproxy.* mappings, geoip.* mappings. Delete @cf.origin and *.cf_ignored_app fields (these fields have constant values).
    
    * Rename "APP/PROC/WEB" to just "APP" for simplicity.
    
    * Rework fields @source.index, .job_index and .vm
    
    App logs and platform logs from syslog release pass `job_index` field which is string bosh instance id. So we parse this field and store it as `@source.job_index`.
    Platform logs from metron agent pass `index` field which is numeric instance number. We store this field as `@source.index`. Additionally in this case, we set `@source.vm` field calculated as `job`/`index` (similar to how Logsearch sets it for Nats logs).
    
    Change parsing rules, tests and mappings accordingly.
    
    * Add mappings for new rtr fields
    
    * Update documentation for mappings
    adds working pattern for cf release v252+
    Fix RTR parsing
    
    Extend RTR grok pattern with destIPandPort value.
    https://github.com/cloudfoundry-community/logsearch-for-cloudfoundry/issues/217
    Make rtr.@message more specific
    Fix parsing tests. Add tests for new parsing rules.
    Add parsing of different app events
    
    1. Set [@source][type] from dictionary for all events; additionally override it with source_event for LogMessage events.
    2. Change parsing of LogMessage, ContainerMetric to make generic solution for all event types. Add parsing of missing event types: Error, ValueMetric, CounterEvent, HttpStart, HttpStop, HttpStartStop.
    3. Rename snippets to make their names reflect the events they parse.
    Fields rework
    
    Make the same platform and app fields consistent, add useful fields.
    
    1. Sync. app basic fields (@source etc.) with platform fields (so that both indices have the same basic fields); Platform: set @source.origin field to 'system'/'cf'.
    2. Store app specific json cf_ fields to @cf;
    3. Set @type to specific values for platform logs (uaa, haproxy or vcap);
    4. Set parsed_json_data_field_name to handle name of parsed json field. We store app parsed json to field named of @type (e.g. rtr, app etc.). And we store vcap message parsed json and app msg parsed json to field named of @source.component value;
    5. App parsing: store event_type to @type, source_type to @source.type.
    6. Rename parsed_json_data to parsed_json_field.
    7. Add field @index_type to store platform/app value.
    8. Update ES mappings and Kibana objects accordingly.
    General refactoring
    
    1) refactoring in snippets (optimize filters, fix formatting, comments)
    2) refactoring in UTs (change checks to get fail-fast for not-related fields, fix describe messages, improve checks)
    3) add haproxy fail grok unit test case
    4) rename vcap fail json tag
    Fields rework
    
    1. Remove _logstash_input field (we don't need it because we have @input field containing value of log input)
    2. Do not rename tags to @tags. This is incorrect to rename tags because logsearch-boshrelease also sets some tags after logsearch-for-cloudfoundry filters processed.
    3. Simplified if checks in snippets
    4. Reworked @type field
    5. Get rid of unparsed index (default index is platform)
    6. Update tests

    Haproxy grok formats + http_status_code check

    Fields refactoring
    
    Add @input field. Remove syslog_pid; Remove [@job][host].
    Set [@source][host] where it was missing.
    Set @message for uaa.
    Check JSON format more strictly (vcap).
    Rename grok fail tag (undefined);
    Remove square brackets where we access simple fields (e.g. use @level instead of [@level]).
    Unify events timestamp by setting 'date' from metron_agent timestamp
    
    Do not set event 'date' from specific logs timestamp fields anymore. Set it from metron_agent timestamp instead (to have time consistency between logs of different sources).
    Fix firehose parsing to set 'date' from <JSON>.timestamp field instead of <JSON>.time because in fact 'timestamp' is right field that contains timestamp from metron_agent (see https://github.com/cloudfoundry-community/firehose-to-syslog/issues/79 for description of time fields in firehose JSON).
    Filters decomposition & additional processing
    
    Filters decomosition:
    Move common 'init' logic to 'setup' script and call it from default.conf.erb before all snippets. Similarly move all common 'cleanup' logic to teardown.conf and call it after all snippets.
    
    Additional procesing:
    1) Add processing of undefined CF logs in undefined.conf snippet (parsing of those logs that are not parsed by any of existing special snippets like uaa, vcap etc.).
    2) Make teardown.conf set @level and @source.component fields from corresponding syslog* fields if they haven't been set in snippets (we need to have at least some value for these fields cause they are significant some).

    Rename `@source.instance` to `@source.job_index` (string guid), cease @source.name field
    
    https://github.com/cloudfoundry-community/logsearch-for-cloudfoundry/issues/217 (a change for job_index)
    Because `Index` field passed from Loggregator (doppler) was changed from uint instance number to guid instance ID, and firefox-to-syslog renamed `index` to `job_index`, the following changes were done in parsing:
    1. `@source.instance` renamed to `@source.job_index`. It's datatype changed from int to string - so no more converting to int is necessary.
    2. Because `source.job_index` is no more a short index of a job instance, but its bosh ID, we cease `@source.name` field (calculated as job+index before).
    3. Update Uindices and Kibana saved objects accordingly. Update UTs.

    5. App parsing: store event_type to @type, source_type to @source.type.

    Store parsed json to a field with name of @source.component
    
    Different vcap components have different JSON messages, but could contain JSON fields with the same name and different type. This causes Logstash warning and lose of data. So we store parsed JSON to a field named like @source.component so that different components do not intersect in naming of JSON fields.

    2. Store app specific json cf_ fields to @cf;
    3. Set @type to specific values for platform logs (uaa, haproxy or vcap);
    4. Set parsed_json_data_field_name to handle name of parsed json field. We store app parsed json to field named of @type (e.g. rtr, app etc.). And we store vcap message parsed json and app msg parsed json to field named of @source.component value;
    5. App parsing: store event_type to @type, source_type to @source.type.
    6. Rename parsed_json_data to parsed_json_field.
    7. Add field @index_type to store platform/app value.
    8. Update ES mappings and Kibana objects accordingly.
    Fix: do not drop app events with empty [msg] for events other than LogMessage
    
    Actually events of other types (CounterEvent, ValueMetric etc.) are usually set with empty [msg] by firehose-to-syslog tool because they are metric events and don't encapsulate actual message.
    When parsing we used to drop all app events with empty/blank [msg] field. But we should apply this logic to LogMessage only. So this logic was moved from app.conf to app-log.conf and now only LogMessage events are dropped when contain empty/blank [msg] field. Update tests accordingly. Add IT with drop/keep event check.
    General refactoring
    
    1) refactoring in snippets (optimize filters, fix formatting, comments)
    2) refactoring in UTs (change checks to get fail-fast for not-related fields, fix describe messages, improve checks)
    3) add haproxy fail grok unit test case
    4) rename vcap fail json tag
    Fields rework
    
    1. Remove _logstash_input field (we don't need it because we have @input field containing value of log input)
    2. Do not rename tags to @tags. This is incorrect to rename tags because logsearch-boshrelease also sets some tags after logsearch-for-cloudfoundry filters processed.
    3. Simplified if checks in snippets
    4. Reworked @type field
    5. Get rid of unparsed index (default index is platform)
    6. Update tests
    Uppercase [@source][component] in app logs
    
    The thing is that Dea CF used to pass 'App' source_type in app logs (while passing other sources uppercase e.g. 'RTR', 'STG' etc.).
    New Diego CF passes all sources as uppercase. So we uppercase [@source][component] after parsing source_type to make it conventional.
    
    Update unit tests accordingly. Also add integration tests (testing LogMessage APP events) for both cases - Diego CF and Dea CF.
    Do useful refactoring in app-it-spec.rb to make adding new tests to it easier.
    Split firehose snippet to several & Add UTs for app filters & refactoring in tests
    
    1) Split firehose snippet to several app* snippets for easier maintenance.
    2) Add UTs for app filters.
    3) Minor refactoring in existing tests.
    Change UAA parsing to parse all UAA events
    
    We used to parse only UAA Audit events before. Change parsing rules to 1) parse UAA log using general format of UAA events 2) Additionaly parse Audit events using their specific message format.
    Update tests accordingly.
    
    Change Kibana objects for UAA to UAA Audit.

    2. Store app specific json cf_ fields to @cf;
    3. Set @type to specific values for platform logs (uaa, haproxy or vcap);
    4. Set parsed_json_data_field_name to handle name of parsed json field. We store app parsed json to field named of @type (e.g. rtr, app etc.). And we store vcap message parsed json and app msg parsed json to field named of @source.component value;
    5. App parsing: store event_type to @type, source_type to @source.type.

    Filters: Add support of integration tests & Add first integration tests & Refactoring of common fields

    Clarify haproxy grok patterns & Add UTs for haproxy-spec.rb  …
    1) Clrify haproxy grok patterns based on haproxy specification (http://www.haproxy.org/download/1.7/doc/configuration.txt)
    2) Add UTs for haproxy parsing rules
    3) Minor: fix uaa grok fail tag name (to be convenient with other snippets)
    Remove outdated UTs & Add UTs for UAA snippet
    Platform filters decomposition
    
    Move common platform logs parsing to a separate snippet - platform.conf.
    
    New snippet platform.conf combines deleted undefined.conf and platform filtering common logic.
    So platform.conf snippet now parses logs using general CF logs format (metron_agent format) + sets common fields. Other platform snippets are applied afterwards.
    Fields refactoring
    
    Add @input field. Remove syslog_pid; Remove [@job][host].
    Set [@source][host] where it was missing.
    Set @message for uaa.
    Check JSON format more strictly (vcap).
    Rename grok fail tag (undefined);
    Remove square brackets where we access simple fields (e.g. use @level instead of [@level]).
    Unify events timestamp by setting 'date' from metron_agent timestamp
    
    Do not set event 'date' from specific logs timestamp fields anymore. Set it from metron_agent timestamp instead (to have time consistency between logs of different sources).
    Fix firehose parsing to set 'date' from <JSON>.timestamp field instead of <JSON>.time because in fact 'timestamp' is right field that contains timestamp from metron_agent (see https://github.com/cloudfoundry-community/firehose-to-syslog/issues/79 for description of time fields in firehose JSON).
    Filters decomposition & additional processing
    
    Filters decomosition:
    Move common 'init' logic to 'setup' script and call it from default.conf.erb before all snippets. Similarly move all common 'cleanup' logic to teardown.conf and call it after all snippets.
    
    Additional procesing:
    1) Add processing of undefined CF logs in undefined.conf snippet (parsing of those logs that are not parsed by any of existing special snippets like uaa, vcap etc.).
    2) Make teardown.conf set @level and @source.component fields from corresponding syslog* fields if they haven't been set in snippets (we need to have at least some value for these fields cause they are significant some).
    Filters refactoring & rework:
    1) Rewrite firehose and uaa snippets to follow common scripts structure. Minor changes in comments.
    2) Uaa, firehose: add @shipper.* fields; do not use old 'remove' option in mutate (replaced with 'remove_field'); lowercase UAA fields (UAA.* -> uaa.*).
    3) Firehose: replace unicode Null character (\0000) with "" and drop empty logs; fixed convertion of HTTP status code to @level.
    4) Common fields changes: uppercase @level field; rename field tags -> @tags.

    Rework ES mappings (#242)
    
    * Rework mappings
    
    Add static mappings for parsed fields. Rework mappings. Use properties
    for app and platform index names. Fix some fields parsing
    (@shipper.priority).
    
    * Fix haproxy.* mappings, geoip.* mappings. Delete @cf.origin and *.cf_ignored_app fields (these fields have constant values).
    
    * Rename "APP/PROC/WEB" to just "APP" for simplicity.
    
    * Rework fields @source.index, .job_index and .vm
    
    App logs and platform logs from syslog release pass `job_index` field which is string bosh instance id. So we parse this field and store it as `@source.job_index`.
    Platform logs from metron agent pass `index` field which is numeric instance number. We store this field as `@source.index`. Additionally in this case, we set `@source.vm` field calculated as `job`/`index` (similar to how Logsearch sets it for Nats logs).
    
    Change parsing rules, tests and mappings accordingly.
    
    * Add mappings for new rtr fields
    
    * Update documentation for mappings
    Get rid of HttpStart, HttpStop events processing
    
    Recently, dropsonde protocol removed HttpStart and HttpStop events,
    leaving HttpStartStop only (https://github.com/cloudfoundry/dropsonde-protocol/commit/3dd1473786cf6acdcc55e2206a58f08ad02f29ca). Even though current version of firehose-to-syslog is still uses these events processing, current versions of CloudFoundry don't operate these events, because they use latest dropsonde protocol. So we can get rid of these events in Logsearch-for-cloudfoundry to simplify processing.
    Rename `@source.instance` to `@source.job_index` (string guid), cease @source.name field
    
    https://github.com/cloudfoundry-community/logsearch-for-cloudfoundry/issues/217 (a change for job_index)
    Because `Index` field passed from Loggregator (doppler) was changed from uint instance number to guid instance ID, and firefox-to-syslog renamed `index` to `job_index`, the following changes were done in parsing:
    1. `@source.instance` renamed to `@source.job_index`. It's datatype changed from int to string - so no more converting to int is necessary.
    2. Because `source.job_index` is no more a short index of a job instance, but its bosh ID, we cease `@source.name` field (calculated as job+index before).
    3. Update Uindices and Kibana saved objects accordingly. Update UTs.
    Add parsing of different app events
    
    1. Set [@source][type] from dictionary for all events; additionally override it with source_event for LogMessage events.
    2. Change parsing of LogMessage, ContainerMetric to make generic solution for all event types. Add parsing of missing event types: Error, ValueMetric, CounterEvent, HttpStart, HttpStop, HttpStartStop.
    3. Rename snippets to make their names reflect the events they parse.
    Fields rework
    
    Make the same platform and app fields consistent, add useful fields.
    
    1. Sync. app basic fields (@source etc.) with platform fields (so that both indices have the same basic fields); Platform: set @source.origin field to 'system'/'cf'.
    2. Store app specific json cf_ fields to @cf;
    3. Set @type to specific values for platform logs (uaa, haproxy or vcap);
    4. Set parsed_json_data_field_name to handle name of parsed json field. We store app parsed json to field named of @type (e.g. rtr, app etc.). And we store vcap message parsed json and app msg parsed json to field named of @source.component value;
    5. App parsing: store event_type to @type, source_type to @source.type.
    6. Rename parsed_json_data to parsed_json_field.
    7. Add field @index_type to store platform/app value.
    8. Update ES mappings and Kibana objects accordingly.

    Store parsed json to a field with name of @source.component
    
    Different vcap components have different JSON messages, but could contain JSON fields with the same name and different type. This causes Logstash warning and lose of data. So we store parsed JSON to a field named like @source.component so that different components do not intersect in naming of JSON fields.

    Add test for the empty BOSH director name in syslog fields
    
    This is a default value in syslog-release
    https://github.com/cloudfoundry/syslog-release/blob/8b44d5e3e2f04109d058c3602315f20a1a6746d8/jobs/syslog_forwarder/spec#L29
    Add missing fields to @source from syslog_sd_params
    Handle RFC 5424 syslog format for CF platform logs
    
    The latest syslog-release project introduced a new Syslog log format which is
    based on RFC 5424 [1]. This format is automatically parsed by the Logstash
    filters defined in [2] therefore the grok filters will fail in platform.conf.
    
    We check for syslog_sd_id first and make sure the common fields and tags are set.
    
    [1] https://github.com/cloudfoundry/syslog-release/blob/e58e88281429f0bac1313994db447fce22b29106/jobs/syslog_forwarder/templates/rsyslog.conf.erb#L54
    [2] https://github.com/cloudfoundry-community/logsearch-boshrelease/blob/9c0376bfd403cc63df058a30e6e27e4f0b41c889/src/logsearch-config/src/logstash-filters/snippets/syslog_standard.conf#L3

    Translate numeric @level to string value
    Fix parsing tests. Add tests for new parsing rules.
    Fields rework
    
    Make the same platform and app fields consistent, add useful fields.
    
    1. Sync. app basic fields (@source etc.) with platform fields (so that both indices have the same basic fields); Platform: set @source.origin field to 'system'/'cf'.
    2. Store app specific json cf_ fields to @cf;
    3. Set @type to specific values for platform logs (uaa, haproxy or vcap);
    4. Set parsed_json_data_field_name to handle name of parsed json field. We store app parsed json to field named of @type (e.g. rtr, app etc.). And we store vcap message parsed json and app msg parsed json to field named of @source.component value;
    5. App parsing: store event_type to @type, source_type to @source.type.
    6. Rename parsed_json_data to parsed_json_field.
    7. Add field @index_type to store platform/app value.
    8. Update ES mappings and Kibana objects accordingly.
    General refactoring
    
    1) refactoring in snippets (optimize filters, fix formatting, comments)
    2) refactoring in UTs (change checks to get fail-fast for not-related fields, fix describe messages, improve checks)
    3) add haproxy fail grok unit test case
    4) rename vcap fail json tag
    Rename snippets
    
    Rename snippets to bring more clarity into their functional purpose.
    Fields rework
    
    1. Remove _logstash_input field (we don't need it because we have @input field containing value of log input)
    2. Do not rename tags to @tags. This is incorrect to rename tags because logsearch-boshrelease also sets some tags after logsearch-for-cloudfoundry filters processed.
    3. Simplified if checks in snippets
    4. Reworked @type field
    5. Get rid of unparsed index (default index is platform)
    6. Update tests
    Store parsed json to a field with name of @source.component
    
    Different vcap components have different JSON messages, but could contain JSON fields with the same name and different type. This causes Logstash warning and lose of data. So we store parsed JSON to a field named like @source.component so that different components do not intersect in naming of JSON fields.

    1) Add UTs for vcap.conf, platform.conf, setup.conf, teardown.conf;
    2) Uaa & haproxy UTs: add checks for 'if' condition;
    3) Improve filter_test_helpers.rb & existing tests to have more smart printing in case of errors.

    Add a logmessage_rtr config for new gorouter_time and app_time fields (#337)
    
    These fields were introduced in routing-release 0.196.0 https://github.com/cloudfoundry/routing-release/releases/tag/0.196.0 which forms part of cf-deployment v12.17.0 https://github.com/cloudfoundry/cf-deployment/releases/tag/v12.17.0

    Add [rtr][response_time_ms] without using the ruby filter (#287)
    
    We want to use a 3rd party ELK stack where there ruby filter plugin is not
    enabled for security reasons. This commit adds the response_time_ms using gsub.
    The value is truncated at three digits (instead of rounding).

    Rework ES mappings (#242)
    
    * Rework mappings
    
    Add static mappings for parsed fields. Rework mappings. Use properties
    for app and platform index names. Fix some fields parsing
    (@shipper.priority).
    
    * Fix haproxy.* mappings, geoip.* mappings. Delete @cf.origin and *.cf_ignored_app fields (these fields have constant values).
    
    * Rename "APP/PROC/WEB" to just "APP" for simplicity.
    
    * Rework fields @source.index, .job_index and .vm
    
    App logs and platform logs from syslog release pass `job_index` field which is string bosh instance id. So we parse this field and store it as `@source.job_index`.
    Platform logs from metron agent pass `index` field which is numeric instance number. We store this field as `@source.index`. Additionally in this case, we set `@source.vm` field calculated as `job`/`index` (similar to how Logsearch sets it for Nats logs).
    
    Change parsing rules, tests and mappings accordingly.
    
    * Add mappings for new rtr fields
    
    * Update documentation for mappings

    3. Rename snippets to make their names reflect the events they parse.

    Fix app parsing for logs with APP/* source_type fields
    
    https://github.com/cloudfoundry-community/logsearch-for-cloudfoundry/issues/217
    Fix parsing tests. Add tests for new parsing rules.
    Add parsing of different app events
    
    1. Set [@source][type] from dictionary for all events; additionally override it with source_event for LogMessage events.
    2. Change parsing of LogMessage, ContainerMetric to make generic solution for all event types. Add parsing of missing event types: Error, ValueMetric, CounterEvent, HttpStart, HttpStop, HttpStartStop.
    3. Rename snippets to make their names reflect the events they parse.
    Fix: do not drop app events with empty [msg] for events other than LogMessage
    
    Actually events of other types (CounterEvent, ValueMetric etc.) are usually set with empty [msg] by firehose-to-syslog tool because they are metric events and don't encapsulate actual message.
    When parsing we used to drop all app events with empty/blank [msg] field. But we should apply this logic to LogMessage only. So this logic was moved from app.conf to app-log.conf and now only LogMessage events are dropped when contain empty/blank [msg] field. Update tests accordingly. Add IT with drop/keep event check.
    General refactoring
    
    1) refactoring in snippets (optimize filters, fix formatting, comments)
    2) refactoring in UTs (change checks to get fail-fast for not-related fields, fix describe messages, improve checks)
    3) add haproxy fail grok unit test case
    4) rename vcap fail json tag
    Rename snippets
    
    Rename snippets to bring more clarity into their functional purpose.
    Uppercase [@source][component] in app logs
    
    The thing is that Dea CF used to pass 'App' source_type in app logs (while passing other sources uppercase e.g. 'RTR', 'STG' etc.).
    New Diego CF passes all sources as uppercase. So we uppercase [@source][component] after parsing source_type to make it conventional.
    
    Update unit tests accordingly. Also add integration tests (testing LogMessage APP events) for both cases - Diego CF and Dea CF.
    Do useful refactoring in app-it-spec.rb to make adding new tests to it easier.
    Split firehose snippet to several & Add UTs for app filters & refactoring in tests
    
    1) Split firehose snippet to several app* snippets for easier maintenance.
    2) Add UTs for app filters.
    3) Minor refactoring in existing tests.

    Rework ES mappings (#242)
    
    * Rework mappings
    
    Add static mappings for parsed fields. Rework mappings. Use properties
    for app and platform index names. Fix some fields parsing
    (@shipper.priority).
    
    * Fix haproxy.* mappings, geoip.* mappings. Delete @cf.origin and *.cf_ignored_app fields (these fields have constant values).

    * Rework fields @source.index, .job_index and .vm
    
    App logs and platform logs from syslog release pass `job_index` field which is string bosh instance id. So we parse this field and store it as `@source.job_index`.
    Platform logs from metron agent pass `index` field which is numeric instance number. We store this field as `@source.index`. Additionally in this case, we set `@source.vm` field calculated as `job`/`index` (similar to how Logsearch sets it for Nats logs).
    
    Change parsing rules, tests and mappings accordingly.
    
    * Add mappings for new rtr fields
    
    * Update documentation for mappings
    Get rid of HttpStart, HttpStop events processing
    
    Recently, dropsonde protocol removed HttpStart and HttpStop events,
    leaving HttpStartStop only (https://github.com/cloudfoundry/dropsonde-protocol/commit/3dd1473786cf6acdcc55e2206a58f08ad02f29ca). Even though current version of firehose-to-syslog is still uses these events processing, current versions of CloudFoundry don't operate these events, because they use latest dropsonde protocol. So we can get rid of these events in Logsearch-for-cloudfoundry to simplify processing.
    Rename `@source.instance` to `@source.job_index` (string guid), cease @source.name field
    
    https://github.com/cloudfoundry-community/logsearch-for-cloudfoundry/issues/217 (a change for job_index)
    Because `Index` field passed from Loggregator (doppler) was changed from uint instance number to guid instance ID, and firefox-to-syslog renamed `index` to `job_index`, the following changes were done in parsing:
    1. `@source.instance` renamed to `@source.job_index`. It's datatype changed from int to string - so no more converting to int is necessary.
    2. Because `source.job_index` is no more a short index of a job instance, but its bosh ID, we cease `@source.name` field (calculated as job+index before).
    3. Update Uindices and Kibana saved objects accordingly. Update UTs.
    Fix parsing tests. Add tests for new parsing rules.
    Fix: do not drop app events with empty [msg] for events other than LogMessage
    
    Actually events of other types (CounterEvent, ValueMetric etc.) are usually set with empty [msg] by firehose-to-syslog tool because they are metric events and don't encapsulate actual message.
    When parsing we used to drop all app events with empty/blank [msg] field. But we should apply this logic to LogMessage only. So this logic was moved from app.conf to app-log.conf and now only LogMessage events are dropped when contain empty/blank [msg] field. Update tests accordingly. Add IT with drop/keep event check.
    Add a useful test case
    
    Check that we doesn't drop log event when it is missing [msg] field.
    General refactoring
    
    1) refactoring in snippets (optimize filters, fix formatting, comments)
    2) refactoring in UTs (change checks to get fail-fast for not-related fields, fix describe messages, improve checks)
    3) add haproxy fail grok unit test case
    4) rename vcap fail json tag
    Rename snippets
    
    Rename snippets to bring more clarity into their functional purpose.
    Fields rework
    
    1. Remove _logstash_input field (we don't need it because we have @input field containing value of log input)
    2. Do not rename tags to @tags. This is incorrect to rename tags because logsearch-boshrelease also sets some tags after logsearch-for-cloudfoundry filters processed.
    3. Simplified if checks in snippets
    4. Reworked @type field
    5. Get rid of unparsed index (default index is platform)
    6. Update tests
    Uppercase [@source][component] in app logs
    
    The thing is that Dea CF used to pass 'App' source_type in app logs (while passing other sources uppercase e.g. 'RTR', 'STG' etc.).
    New Diego CF passes all sources as uppercase. So we uppercase [@source][component] after parsing source_type to make it conventional.
    
    Update unit tests accordingly. Also add integration tests (testing LogMessage APP events) for both cases - Diego CF and Dea CF.

    Rework ES mappings (#242)
    
    * Rework mappings
    
    Add static mappings for parsed fields. Rework mappings. Use properties
    for app and platform index names. Fix some fields parsing
    (@shipper.priority).
    
    * Fix haproxy.* mappings, geoip.* mappings. Delete @cf.origin and *.cf_ignored_app fields (these fields have constant values).
    
    * Rename "APP/PROC/WEB" to just "APP" for simplicity.
    
    * Rework fields @source.index, .job_index and .vm
    
    App logs and platform logs from syslog release pass `job_index` field which is string bosh instance id. So we parse this field and store it as `@source.job_index`.
    Platform logs from metron agent pass `index` field which is numeric instance number. We store this field as `@source.index`. Additionally in this case, we set `@source.vm` field calculated as `job`/`index` (similar to how Logsearch sets it for Nats logs).
    
    Change parsing rules, tests and mappings accordingly.
    
    * Add mappings for new rtr fields
    
    * Update documentation for mappings
    Rename `@source.instance` to `@source.job_index` (string guid), cease @source.name field
    
    https://github.com/cloudfoundry-community/logsearch-for-cloudfoundry/issues/217 (a change for job_index)
    Because `Index` field passed from Loggregator (doppler) was changed from uint instance number to guid instance ID, and firefox-to-syslog renamed `index` to `job_index`, the following changes were done in parsing:
    1. `@source.instance` renamed to `@source.job_index`. It's datatype changed from int to string - so no more converting to int is necessary.
    2. Because `source.job_index` is no more a short index of a job instance, but its bosh ID, we cease `@source.name` field (calculated as job+index before).
    3. Update Uindices and Kibana saved objects accordingly. Update UTs.
    Support for cloudfoundry/syslog-release log messages
    
    Fix for https://github.com/cloudfoundry-community/logsearch-for-cloudfoundry/issues/204.
    Change UAA parsing to parse all UAA events
    
    We used to parse only UAA Audit events before. Change parsing rules to 1) parse UAA log using general format of UAA events 2) Additionaly parse Audit events using their specific message format.
    Update tests accordingly.
    
    Change Kibana objects for UAA to UAA Audit.
    Update Kibana searches, visualizations, dashboards
    
    1. Add/fix Kibana searches, visualizations, dashboards. Delete outdated stuff.
    2. Fix haproxy parsing by converting numeric fields ti int to make it possible use them in analytics.
    3. Update index_template mappings (add haproxy.request_verb.raw not_analyzed field to make it possible to use it in visualizations).
    Rework ITs. Add ITs for all app event types.
    Fix parsing tests. Add tests for new parsing rules.
    Fields rework
    
    Make the same platform and app fields consistent, add useful fields.
    
    1. Sync. app basic fields (@source etc.) with platform fields (so that both indices have the same basic fields); Platform: set @source.origin field to 'system'/'cf'.
    2. Store app specific json cf_ fields to @cf;
    3. Set @type to specific values for platform logs (uaa, haproxy or vcap);
    4. Set parsed_json_data_field_name to handle name of parsed json field. We store app parsed json to field named of @type (e.g. rtr, app etc.). And we store vcap message parsed json and app msg parsed json to field named of @source.component value;
    5. App parsing: store event_type to @type, source_type to @source.type.
    6. Rename parsed_json_data to parsed_json_field.
    7. Add field @index_type to store platform/app value.
    8. Update ES mappings and Kibana objects accordingly.
    Rename snippets
    
    Rename snippets to bring more clarity into their functional purpose.
    Fields rework
    
    1. Remove _logstash_input field (we don't need it because we have @input field containing value of log input)
    2. Do not rename tags to @tags. This is incorrect to rename tags because logsearch-boshrelease also sets some tags after logsearch-for-cloudfoundry filters processed.
    3. Simplified if checks in snippets
    4. Reworked @type field
    5. Get rid of unparsed index (default index is platform)
    6. Update tests
    Store parsed json to a field with name of @source.component
    
    Different vcap components have different JSON messages, but could contain JSON fields with the same name and different type. This causes Logstash warning and lose of data. So we store parsed JSON to a field named like @source.component so that different components do not intersect in naming of JSON fields.
    Add filters integration tests
    Add more UTs & improve existing
    
    1) Add UTs for vcap.conf, platform.conf, setup.conf, teardown.conf;
    2) Uaa & haproxy UTs: add checks for 'if' condition;
    3) Improve filter_test_helpers.rb & existing tests to have more smart printing in case of errors.
    Filters: Add support of integration tests & Add first integration tests & Refactoring of common fields
    
    1) Add support of integration tests. Integration tests run as part of all tests run and also can be started separately by executing bin/itest.
    2) Add first integration tests (app and platform cases checking common fields).
    3) Move parsing of common fields from snippets to setup.conf script. Snippets can override common fields with specific values if necessary.
    4) Minor refactoring & comments.

    Rework ES mappings (#242)
    
    * Rework mappings
    
    Add static mappings for parsed fields. Rework mappings. Use properties

    App logs and platform logs from syslog release pass `job_index` field which is string bosh instance id. So we parse this field and store it as `@source.job_index`.
    Platform logs from metron agent pass `index` field which is numeric instance number. We store this field as `@source.index`. Additionally in this case, we set `@source.vm` field calculated as `job`/`index` (similar to how Logsearch sets it for Nats logs).

    * Add mappings for new rtr fields
    
    * Update documentation for mappings
    adds working pattern for cf release v252+
    Get rid of HttpStart, HttpStop events processing
    
    Recently, dropsonde protocol removed HttpStart and HttpStop events,
    leaving HttpStartStop only (https://github.com/cloudfoundry/dropsonde-protocol/commit/3dd1473786cf6acdcc55e2206a58f08ad02f29ca). Even though current version of firehose-to-syslog is still uses these events processing, current versions of CloudFoundry don't operate these events, because they use latest dropsonde protocol. So we can get rid of these events in Logsearch-for-cloudfoundry to simplify processing.
    Make rtr.@message more specific
    Change parsing rules after recent fields fixes in firehose-to-syslog 2.0.0
    Rework ITs. Add ITs for all app event types.
    Fix parsing tests. Add tests for new parsing rules.
    Fix: do not drop app events with empty [msg] for events other than LogMessage
    
    Actually events of other types (CounterEvent, ValueMetric etc.) are usually set with empty [msg] by firehose-to-syslog tool because they are metric events and don't encapsulate actual message.
    When parsing we used to drop all app events with empty/blank [msg] field. But we should apply this logic to LogMessage only. So this logic was moved from app.conf to app-log.conf and now only LogMessage events are dropped when contain empty/blank [msg] field. Update tests accordingly. Add IT with drop/keep event check.
    Rename snippets
    
    Rename snippets to bring more clarity into their functional purpose.
    Fields rework
    
    1. Remove _logstash_input field (we don't need it because we have @input field containing value of log input)
    2. Do not rename tags to @tags. This is incorrect to rename tags because logsearch-boshrelease also sets some tags after logsearch-for-cloudfoundry filters processed.
    3. Simplified if checks in snippets
    4. Reworked @type field
    5. Get rid of unparsed index (default index is platform)
    6. Update tests
    Store parsed json to a field with name of @source.component
    
    Different vcap components have different JSON messages, but could contain JSON fields with the same name and different type. This causes Logstash warning and lose of data. So we store parsed JSON to a field named like @source.component so that different components do not intersect in naming of JSON fields.
    Firehose parsing: parse new fields
    
    Recent version of firehose-to-syslog passes new fields in json message: deployment, ip, job. Add parsing rules for these fields. Update tests accordingly.
    Uppercase [@source][component] in app logs
    
    The thing is that Dea CF used to pass 'App' source_type in app logs (while passing other sources uppercase e.g. 'RTR', 'STG' etc.).
    New Diego CF passes all sources as uppercase. So we uppercase [@source][component] after parsing source_type to make it conventional.
    
    Update unit tests accordingly. Also add integration tests (testing LogMessage APP events) for both cases - Diego CF and Dea CF.
    Do useful refactoring in app-it-spec.rb to make adding new tests to it easier.

    1) Split firehose snippet to several app* snippets for easier maintenance.

    3) Minor refactoring in existing tests.
    Add filters integration tests

    2) Add first integration tests (app and platform cases checking common fields).

    Use bosh-packages/ruby-release 2.4-r5
    Make prefix of index pattern in ES settings/mappings configurable
    
    Move index templates from package `logsearch-config-es-mappings` to job `elasticsearch-config-lfc` in order to use deploy properties. Split predefined index template into two: 1st) configures index settings that will be merged with those defined in Logsearch 2nd) configures index mappings. Make index templates use property `elasticsearch_config.index_prefix`.
    Split packages (#221)
    
    * Split logsearch-for-cloudfoundry-filters job
    
    Instead of one job (and one package) logserach-for-cloudfoundry-filters,
    which actually included also es-mappings and kibana-saved-objects, we now
    split it and have three separate jobs (and packages accordingly):
    logsearch-config-logstash-filters, logserach-config-es-mappings and
    logsearch-config-kibana-objects.
    
    * Revert custom settings in template
    Avoid pre_packaging in logsearch-for-cloudfoundry-filters package
    add cf-kibaba job
    deploy cloudfoundry operator log parsing rules to VMs

    [#112137913]
    
    Signed-off-by: Alex Blease <ablease@pivotal.io>
    Pull boshrelease into root of repo
    logsearch-for-cloudfoundry-boshrelease based on firehose-to-syslog v0.0.1
    Update troubleshooting.md
    Update troubleshooting.md
    Write up-to-date documentation
    Spelling (#256)
    Rework ES mappings (#242)
    
    * Rework mappings
    
    Add static mappings for parsed fields. Rework mappings. Use properties
    for app and platform index names. Fix some fields parsing
    (@shipper.priority).
    
    * Fix haproxy.* mappings, geoip.* mappings. Delete @cf.origin and *.cf_ignored_app fields (these fields have constant values).
    
    * Rename "APP/PROC/WEB" to just "APP" for simplicity.
    
    * Rework fields @source.index, .job_index and .vm
    
    App logs and platform logs from syslog release pass `job_index` field which is string bosh instance id. So we parse this field and store it as `@source.job_index`.
    Platform logs from metron agent pass `index` field which is numeric instance number. We store this field as `@source.index`. Additionally in this case, we set `@source.vm` field calculated as `job`/`index` (similar to how Logsearch sets it for Nats logs).
    
    Change parsing rules, tests and mappings accordingly.
    
    * Add mappings for new rtr fields
    
    * Update documentation for mappings
    Get rid of HttpStart, HttpStop events processing
    
    Recently, dropsonde protocol removed HttpStart and HttpStop events,
    leaving HttpStartStop only (https://github.com/cloudfoundry/dropsonde-protocol/commit/3dd1473786cf6acdcc55e2206a58f08ad02f29ca). Even though current version of firehose-to-syslog is still uses these events processing, current versions of CloudFoundry don't operate these events, because they use latest dropsonde protocol. So we can get rid of these events in Logsearch-for-cloudfoundry to simplify processing.
    Upload Kibana objects based on `firehose_events` property (#223)
    
    Kibana objects are moved from package to job to be loaded based on `firehose_events` deploy property.
    Split packages (#221)
    
    * Split logsearch-for-cloudfoundry-filters job
    
    Instead of one job (and one package) logserach-for-cloudfoundry-filters,
    which actually included also es-mappings and kibana-saved-objects, we now
    split it and have three separate jobs (and packages accordingly):
    logsearch-config-logstash-filters, logserach-config-es-mappings and
    logsearch-config-kibana-objects.
    
    * Revert custom settings in template
    Rename `@source.instance` to `@source.job_index` (string guid), cease @source.name field
    
    https://github.com/cloudfoundry-community/logsearch-for-cloudfoundry/issues/217 (a change for job_index)
    Because `Index` field passed from Loggregator (doppler) was changed from uint instance number to guid instance ID, and firefox-to-syslog renamed `index` to `job_index`, the following changes were done in parsing:
    1. `@source.instance` renamed to `@source.job_index`. It's datatype changed from int to string - so no more converting to int is necessary.
    2. Because `source.job_index` is no more a short index of a job instance, but its bosh ID, we cease `@source.name` field (calculated as job+index before).
    3. Update Uindices and Kibana saved objects accordingly. Update UTs.
    Rework deploy documentation and some properties
    
    1. Add admin_user.name property instead of hardcoded "admin" user
    2. Rename cf-kibana.use_existing_client to cf-kibana.oauth2_use_existing_client
    3. Rename cf-kibana properties connected to CF to cf-kibana.cloudfoundry.*
    4. Move logstash_parser properties to parser job in
    stub.logsearch-for-cloudfoundry.yml (so that cluster_monitor doesn't use
    these properties)
    5. Use my_ values for stubs in deploy templates
    6. Add comments to deploy templates
    7. Grab properties to set Kibana env
    8. Rename logstash_parser.elasticsearch_index* to
    logstash_parser.elasticsearch.index* to be compatible with
    logsearch-boshrelease.parser job spec.
    Write up-to-date documentation
    Update links to logsearch-boshrelease repo
    Write up-to-date documentation
    Add custom filters option (#255)
    
    Allow passing new logstash filters directly from the new
    logstash_parser.custom_filters property. The whole string
    is written to file
    /var/vcap/jobs/logsearch-for-cloudfoundry-filters/config/logstash-filters-custom.conf
    
    The path must be loaded via property logstash_parser.filters similarly to
    how logstash-filters-default.conf is loaded in
    https://github.com/cloudfoundry-community/logsearch-for-cloudfoundry/blob/develop/docs/customization.md#parsing-rules
    
    The customization doc has been updated to describe the new property.

    Set firehose event types as array
    Add support for BOSH links
    Drop square brackets in file names for simpler glob matching. (#259)

    Rework ES mappings (#242)
    
    * Rework mappings
    
    Add static mappings for parsed fields. Rework mappings. Use properties
    for app and platform index names. Fix some fields parsing
    (@shipper.priority).
    
    * Fix haproxy.* mappings, geoip.* mappings. Delete @cf.origin and *.cf_ignored_app fields (these fields have constant values).
    
    * Rename "APP/PROC/WEB" to just "APP" for simplicity.
    
    * Rework fields @source.index, .job_index and .vm
    
    App logs and platform logs from syslog release pass `job_index` field which is string bosh instance id. So we parse this field and store it as `@source.job_index`.
    Platform logs from metron agent pass `index` field which is numeric instance number. We store this field as `@source.index`. Additionally in this case, we set `@source.vm` field calculated as `job`/`index` (similar to how Logsearch sets it for Nats logs).
    
    Change parsing rules, tests and mappings accordingly.
    
    * Add mappings for new rtr fields
    
    * Update documentation for mappings
    Get rid of HttpStart, HttpStop events processing
    
    Recently, dropsonde protocol removed HttpStart and HttpStop events,
    leaving HttpStartStop only (https://github.com/cloudfoundry/dropsonde-protocol/commit/3dd1473786cf6acdcc55e2206a58f08ad02f29ca). Even though current version of firehose-to-syslog is still uses these events processing, current versions of CloudFoundry don't operate these events, because they use latest dropsonde protocol. So we can get rid of these events in Logsearch-for-cloudfoundry to simplify processing.
    Upload Kibana objects based on `firehose_events` property (#223)
    
    Kibana objects are moved from package to job to be loaded based on `firehose_events` deploy property.
    Split packages (#221)
    
    * Split logsearch-for-cloudfoundry-filters job
    
    Instead of one job (and one package) logserach-for-cloudfoundry-filters,
    which actually included also es-mappings and kibana-saved-objects, we now
    split it and have three separate jobs (and packages accordingly):
    logsearch-config-logstash-filters, logserach-config-es-mappings and
    logsearch-config-kibana-objects.
    
    * Revert custom settings in template
    Make data uploaded as Kibana objects configurable

    name it 'objects' rather than 'dashboards'.

    Rename `@source.instance` to `@source.job_index` (string guid), cease @source.name field
    
    https://github.com/cloudfoundry-community/logsearch-for-cloudfoundry/issues/217 (a change for job_index)
    Because `Index` field passed from Loggregator (doppler) was changed from uint instance number to guid instance ID, and firefox-to-syslog renamed `index` to `job_index`, the following changes were done in parsing:
    1. `@source.instance` renamed to `@source.job_index`. It's datatype changed from int to string - so no more converting to int is necessary.
    2. Because `source.job_index` is no more a short index of a job instance, but its bosh ID, we cease `@source.name` field (calculated as job+index before).
    3. Update Uindices and Kibana saved objects accordingly. Update UTs.
    Rename kibana-dashboards to kibana-objects
    
    Actually we upload not only dashboards but also other Kibana objects
    (searches, visualizations, index patterns). So it's more convenient to
    name it 'objects' rather than 'dashboards'.
    Update Kibana searches, visualizations, dashboards
    
    1. Add/fix Kibana searches, visualizations, dashboards. Delete outdated stuff.
    2. Fix haproxy parsing by converting numeric fields ti int to make it possible use them in analytics.
    3. Update index_template mappings (add haproxy.request_verb.raw not_analyzed field to make it possible to use it in visualizations).
    Fields rework
    
    Make the same platform and app fields consistent, add useful fields.
    
    1. Sync. app basic fields (@source etc.) with platform fields (so that both indices have the same basic fields); Platform: set @source.origin field to 'system'/'cf'.
    2. Store app specific json cf_ fields to @cf;
    3. Set @type to specific values for platform logs (uaa, haproxy or vcap);
    4. Set parsed_json_data_field_name to handle name of parsed json field. We store app parsed json to field named of @type (e.g. rtr, app etc.). And we store vcap message parsed json and app msg parsed json to field named of @source.component value;
    5. App parsing: store event_type to @type, source_type to @source.type.
    6. Rename parsed_json_data to parsed_json_field.
    7. Add field @index_type to store platform/app value.
    8. Update ES mappings and Kibana objects accordingly.
    Reconcile kibana configs with mappings and filters.
    
    * Use raw fields for visualization groups.
    * Replace @source.app.name with @source.app.
    * Use wildcard index patterns.
    Resurrect App dashboards
    Pull boshrelease into root of repo
    Add remaining dashboards

    Extract named Kibana4 dashboard config into separate 'human readable' file, combine back into bulk insert request via bin/build

    2. Fix haproxy parsing by converting numeric fields ti int to make it possible use them in analytics.
    3. Update index_template mappings (add haproxy.request_verb.raw not_analyzed field to make it possible to use it in visualizations).

    Use Kibana Saved Objects API (#319)
    
    * Update Kibana objects to support Saved Objects API

    * Generate Kibana objects in separate task

    Update savedSearchIds in Kibana objects
    Upload Kibana objects based on `firehose_events` property (#223)
    
    Kibana objects are moved from package to job to be loaded based on `firehose_events` deploy property.
    Rename `@source.instance` to `@source.job_index` (string guid), cease @source.name field
    
    https://github.com/cloudfoundry-community/logsearch-for-cloudfoundry/issues/217 (a change for job_index)
    Because `Index` field passed from Loggregator (doppler) was changed from uint instance number to guid instance ID, and firefox-to-syslog renamed `index` to `job_index`, the following changes were done in parsing:
    1. `@source.instance` renamed to `@source.job_index`. It's datatype changed from int to string - so no more converting to int is necessary.
    2. Because `source.job_index` is no more a short index of a job instance, but its bosh ID, we cease `@source.name` field (calculated as job+index before).
    3. Update Uindices and Kibana saved objects accordingly. Update UTs.
    Rename kibana-dashboards to kibana-objects
    
    Actually we upload not only dashboards but also other Kibana objects
    (searches, visualizations, index patterns). So it's more convenient to
    name it 'objects' rather than 'dashboards'.
    Update Kibana searches, visualizations, dashboards
    
    1. Add/fix Kibana searches, visualizations, dashboards. Delete outdated stuff.
    2. Fix haproxy parsing by converting numeric fields ti int to make it possible use them in analytics.
    3. Update index_template mappings (add haproxy.request_verb.raw not_analyzed field to make it possible to use it in visualizations).
    Fields rework
    
    Make the same platform and app fields consistent, add useful fields.
    
    1. Sync. app basic fields (@source etc.) with platform fields (so that both indices have the same basic fields); Platform: set @source.origin field to 'system'/'cf'.
    2. Store app specific json cf_ fields to @cf;
    3. Set @type to specific values for platform logs (uaa, haproxy or vcap);
    4. Set parsed_json_data_field_name to handle name of parsed json field. We store app parsed json to field named of @type (e.g. rtr, app etc.). And we store vcap message parsed json and app msg parsed json to field named of @source.component value;
    5. App parsing: store event_type to @type, source_type to @source.type.
    6. Rename parsed_json_data to parsed_json_field.
    7. Add field @index_type to store platform/app value.
    8. Update ES mappings and Kibana objects accordingly.
    Reconcile kibana configs with mappings and filters.
    
    * Use raw fields for visualization groups.
    * Replace @source.app.name with @source.app.
    * Use wildcard index patterns.

    Drop square brackets in file names for simpler glob matching. (#259)
    Rework ES mappings (#242)
    
    * Rework mappings
    
    Add static mappings for parsed fields. Rework mappings. Use properties
    for app and platform index names. Fix some fields parsing
    (@shipper.priority).
    
    * Fix haproxy.* mappings, geoip.* mappings. Delete @cf.origin and *.cf_ignored_app fields (these fields have constant values).
    
    * Rename "APP/PROC/WEB" to just "APP" for simplicity.
    
    * Rework fields @source.index, .job_index and .vm
    
    App logs and platform logs from syslog release pass `job_index` field which is string bosh instance id. So we parse this field and store it as `@source.job_index`.
    Platform logs from metron agent pass `index` field which is numeric instance number. We store this field as `@source.index`. Additionally in this case, we set `@source.vm` field calculated as `job`/`index` (similar to how Logsearch sets it for Nats logs).
    
    Change parsing rules, tests and mappings accordingly.
    
    * Add mappings for new rtr fields
    
    * Update documentation for mappings
    Upload Kibana objects based on `firehose_events` property (#223)
    
    Kibana objects are moved from package to job to be loaded based on `firehose_events` deploy property.
    Rename `@source.instance` to `@source.job_index` (string guid), cease @source.name field
    
    https://github.com/cloudfoundry-community/logsearch-for-cloudfoundry/issues/217 (a change for job_index)
    Because `Index` field passed from Loggregator (doppler) was changed from uint instance number to guid instance ID, and firefox-to-syslog renamed `index` to `job_index`, the following changes were done in parsing:
    1. `@source.instance` renamed to `@source.job_index`. It's datatype changed from int to string - so no more converting to int is necessary.
    2. Because `source.job_index` is no more a short index of a job instance, but its bosh ID, we cease `@source.name` field (calculated as job+index before).
    3. Update Uindices and Kibana saved objects accordingly. Update UTs.

    name it 'objects' rather than 'dashboards'.

    Fields rework
    
    Make the same platform and app fields consistent, add useful fields.
    
    1. Sync. app basic fields (@source etc.) with platform fields (so that both indices have the same basic fields); Platform: set @source.origin field to 'system'/'cf'.
    2. Store app specific json cf_ fields to @cf;
    3. Set @type to specific values for platform logs (uaa, haproxy or vcap);
    4. Set parsed_json_data_field_name to handle name of parsed json field. We store app parsed json to field named of @type (e.g. rtr, app etc.). And we store vcap message parsed json and app msg parsed json to field named of @source.component value;
    5. App parsing: store event_type to @type, source_type to @source.type.
    6. Rename parsed_json_data to parsed_json_field.
    7. Add field @index_type to store platform/app value.
    8. Update ES mappings and Kibana objects accordingly.

    8. Update ES mappings and Kibana objects accordingly.
    Update RTR field names to match logstash templates.
    Reconcile kibana configs with mappings and filters.
    
    * Use raw fields for visualization groups.
    * Replace @source.app.name with @source.app.
    * Use wildcard index patterns.
    Resurrect App dashboards
    Prune down dashboards
    Pull boshrelease into root of repo
    Filter searches by tag rather than _type
    Add UAA-Audit dashboard
    WIP: Extract all dashboards
    Extract named Kibana4 dashboard config into separate 'human readable' file, combine back into bulk insert request via bin/build
    Use Kibana Saved Objects API (#319)
    
    * Update Kibana objects to support Saved Objects API
    * Fix unexpected end-of-input for Kibana objects
    * Add missing ENDOFFJSON
    * Generate Kibana objects in separate task
    * Update index patterns names to make it the same as title
    * Add import objects task
    Drop square brackets in file names for simpler glob matching. (#259)
    Rework ES mappings (#242)
    
    * Rework mappings
    
    Add static mappings for parsed fields. Rework mappings. Use properties
    for app and platform index names. Fix some fields parsing
    (@shipper.priority).
    
    * Fix haproxy.* mappings, geoip.* mappings. Delete @cf.origin and *.cf_ignored_app fields (these fields have constant values).
    
    * Rename "APP/PROC/WEB" to just "APP" for simplicity.
    
    * Rework fields @source.index, .job_index and .vm
    
    App logs and platform logs from syslog release pass `job_index` field which is string bosh instance id. So we parse this field and store it as `@source.job_index`.
    Platform logs from metron agent pass `index` field which is numeric instance number. We store this field as `@source.index`. Additionally in this case, we set `@source.vm` field calculated as `job`/`index` (similar to how Logsearch sets it for Nats logs).
    
    Change parsing rules, tests and mappings accordingly.
    
    * Add mappings for new rtr fields
    
    * Update documentation for mappings
    Upload Kibana objects based on `firehose_events` property (#223)
    
    Kibana objects are moved from package to job to be loaded based on `firehose_events` deploy property.
    Rename kibana-dashboards to kibana-objects
    
    Actually we upload not only dashboards but also other Kibana objects
    (searches, visualizations, index patterns). So it's more convenient to
    name it 'objects' rather than 'dashboards'.
    Update Kibana searches, visualizations, dashboards
    
    1. Add/fix Kibana searches, visualizations, dashboards. Delete outdated stuff.
    2. Fix haproxy parsing by converting numeric fields ti int to make it possible use them in analytics.
    3. Update index_template mappings (add haproxy.request_verb.raw not_analyzed field to make it possible to use it in visualizations).
    Fields rework
    
    Make the same platform and app fields consistent, add useful fields.
    
    1. Sync. app basic fields (@source etc.) with platform fields (so that both indices have the same basic fields); Platform: set @source.origin field to 'system'/'cf'.
    2. Store app specific json cf_ fields to @cf;
    3. Set @type to specific values for platform logs (uaa, haproxy or vcap);
    4. Set parsed_json_data_field_name to handle name of parsed json field. We store app parsed json to field named of @type (e.g. rtr, app etc.). And we store vcap message parsed json and app msg parsed json to field named of @source.component value;
    5. App parsing: store event_type to @type, source_type to @source.type.
    6. Rename parsed_json_data to parsed_json_field.
    7. Add field @index_type to store platform/app value.
    8. Update ES mappings and Kibana objects accordingly.
    Reconcile kibana configs with mappings and filters.
    
    * Use raw fields for visualization groups.
    * Replace @source.app.name with @source.app.
    * Use wildcard index patterns.
    add app container metrics dashboards
