    Fields rework
    
    Make the same platform and app fields consistent, add useful fields.
    
    1. Sync. app basic fields (@source etc.) with platform fields (so that both indices have the same basic fields); Platform: set @source.origin field to 'system'/'cf'.
    2. Store app specific json cf_ fields to @cf;
    3. Set @type to specific values for platform logs (uaa, haproxy or vcap);
    4. Set parsed_json_data_field_name to handle name of parsed json field. We store app parsed json to field named of @type (e.g. rtr, app etc.). And we store vcap message parsed json and app msg parsed json to field named of @source.component value;
    5. App parsing: store event_type to @type, source_type to @source.type.

    Upload Kibana objects based on `firehose_events` property (#223)
    
    Kibana objects are moved from package to job to be loaded based on `firehose_events` deploy property.
    Rename `@source.instance` to `@source.job_index` (string guid), cease @source.name field
    
    https://github.com/cloudfoundry-community/logsearch-for-cloudfoundry/issues/217 (a change for job_index)
    Because `Index` field passed from Loggregator (doppler) was changed from uint instance number to guid instance ID, and firefox-to-syslog renamed `index` to `job_index`, the following changes were done in parsing:
    1. `@source.instance` renamed to `@source.job_index`. It's datatype changed from int to string - so no more converting to int is necessary.
    2. Because `source.job_index` is no more a short index of a job instance, but its bosh ID, we cease `@source.name` field (calculated as job+index before).
    3. Update Uindices and Kibana saved objects accordingly. Update UTs.
    Rename kibana-dashboards to kibana-objects
    
    Actually we upload not only dashboards but also other Kibana objects
    (searches, visualizations, index patterns). So it's more convenient to
    name it 'objects' rather than 'dashboards'.
    Update Kibana searches, visualizations, dashboards
    
    1. Add/fix Kibana searches, visualizations, dashboards. Delete outdated stuff.
    2. Fix haproxy parsing by converting numeric fields ti int to make it possible use them in analytics.
    3. Update index_template mappings (add haproxy.request_verb.raw not_analyzed field to make it possible to use it in visualizations).
    Reconcile kibana configs with mappings and filters.
    
    * Use raw fields for visualization groups.
    * Replace @source.app.name with @source.app.
    * Use wildcard index patterns.

    Pull boshrelease into root of repo
    Filter searches by tag rather than _type
    Add UAA-Audit dashboard

    for app and platform index names. Fix some fields parsing
    (@shipper.priority).
    
    * Fix haproxy.* mappings, geoip.* mappings. Delete @cf.origin and *.cf_ignored_app fields (these fields have constant values).
    
    * Rename "APP/PROC/WEB" to just "APP" for simplicity.
    
    * Rework fields @source.index, .job_index and .vm
    
    App logs and platform logs from syslog release pass `job_index` field which is string bosh instance id. So we parse this field and store it as `@source.job_index`.
    Platform logs from metron agent pass `index` field which is numeric instance number. We store this field as `@source.index`. Additionally in this case, we set `@source.vm` field calculated as `job`/`index` (similar to how Logsearch sets it for Nats logs).
    
    Change parsing rules, tests and mappings accordingly.
    
    * Add mappings for new rtr fields
    
    * Update documentation for mappings
    Upload Kibana objects based on `firehose_events` property (#223)
    
    Kibana objects are moved from package to job to be loaded based on `firehose_events` deploy property.
    Rename kibana-dashboards to kibana-objects
    
    Actually we upload not only dashboards but also other Kibana objects
    (searches, visualizations, index patterns). So it's more convenient to
    name it 'objects' rather than 'dashboards'.
    Update Kibana searches, visualizations, dashboards
    
    1. Add/fix Kibana searches, visualizations, dashboards. Delete outdated stuff.
    2. Fix haproxy parsing by converting numeric fields ti int to make it possible use them in analytics.
    3. Update index_template mappings (add haproxy.request_verb.raw not_analyzed field to make it possible to use it in visualizations).
    Fields rework
    
    Make the same platform and app fields consistent, add useful fields.
    
    1. Sync. app basic fields (@source etc.) with platform fields (so that both indices have the same basic fields); Platform: set @source.origin field to 'system'/'cf'.
    2. Store app specific json cf_ fields to @cf;
    3. Set @type to specific values for platform logs (uaa, haproxy or vcap);
    4. Set parsed_json_data_field_name to handle name of parsed json field. We store app parsed json to field named of @type (e.g. rtr, app etc.). And we store vcap message parsed json and app msg parsed json to field named of @source.component value;
    5. App parsing: store event_type to @type, source_type to @source.type.
    6. Rename parsed_json_data to parsed_json_field.
    7. Add field @index_type to store platform/app value.
    8. Update ES mappings and Kibana objects accordingly.
    Update RTR field names to match logstash templates.
    Reconcile kibana configs with mappings and filters.
    
    * Use raw fields for visualization groups.
    * Replace @source.app.name with @source.app.
    * Use wildcard index patterns.
    Resurrect App dashboards
    Prune down dashboards
    Pull boshrelease into root of repo
    Filter searches by tag rather than _type
    Add UAA-Audit dashboard
    WIP: Extract all dashboards
    Extract named Kibana4 dashboard config into separate 'human readable' file, combine back into bulk insert request via bin/build

    * Generate Kibana objects in separate task

    Upload Kibana objects based on `firehose_events` property (#223)
    
    Kibana objects are moved from package to job to be loaded based on `firehose_events` deploy property.
    Rename `@source.instance` to `@source.job_index` (string guid), cease @source.name field
    
    https://github.com/cloudfoundry-community/logsearch-for-cloudfoundry/issues/217 (a change for job_index)
    Because `Index` field passed from Loggregator (doppler) was changed from uint instance number to guid instance ID, and firefox-to-syslog renamed `index` to `job_index`, the following changes were done in parsing:
    1. `@source.instance` renamed to `@source.job_index`. It's datatype changed from int to string - so no more converting to int is necessary.
    2. Because `source.job_index` is no more a short index of a job instance, but its bosh ID, we cease `@source.name` field (calculated as job+index before).
    3. Update Uindices and Kibana saved objects accordingly. Update UTs.
    Rename kibana-dashboards to kibana-objects
    
    Actually we upload not only dashboards but also other Kibana objects
    (searches, visualizations, index patterns). So it's more convenient to
    name it 'objects' rather than 'dashboards'.
    Update Kibana searches, visualizations, dashboards
    
    1. Add/fix Kibana searches, visualizations, dashboards. Delete outdated stuff.
    2. Fix haproxy parsing by converting numeric fields ti int to make it possible use them in analytics.
    3. Update index_template mappings (add haproxy.request_verb.raw not_analyzed field to make it possible to use it in visualizations).

    * Use wildcard index patterns.

    Add remaining dashboards
    Update UAA-Audit map
    Add UAA-Audit dashboard

    * Rework fields @source.index, .job_index and .vm
    
    App logs and platform logs from syslog release pass `job_index` field which is string bosh instance id. So we parse this field and store it as `@source.job_index`.
    Platform logs from metron agent pass `index` field which is numeric instance number. We store this field as `@source.index`. Additionally in this case, we set `@source.vm` field calculated as `job`/`index` (similar to how Logsearch sets it for Nats logs).
    
    Change parsing rules, tests and mappings accordingly.
    
    * Add mappings for new rtr fields
    
    * Update documentation for mappings
    Upload Kibana objects based on `firehose_events` property (#223)
    
    Kibana objects are moved from package to job to be loaded based on `firehose_events` deploy property.
    Rename kibana-dashboards to kibana-objects
    
    Actually we upload not only dashboards but also other Kibana objects
    (searches, visualizations, index patterns). So it's more convenient to
    name it 'objects' rather than 'dashboards'.
    Update Kibana searches, visualizations, dashboards
    
    1. Add/fix Kibana searches, visualizations, dashboards. Delete outdated stuff.
    2. Fix haproxy parsing by converting numeric fields ti int to make it possible use them in analytics.
    3. Update index_template mappings (add haproxy.request_verb.raw not_analyzed field to make it possible to use it in visualizations).
    Fields rework
    
    Make the same platform and app fields consistent, add useful fields.
    
    1. Sync. app basic fields (@source etc.) with platform fields (so that both indices have the same basic fields); Platform: set @source.origin field to 'system'/'cf'.
    2. Store app specific json cf_ fields to @cf;
    3. Set @type to specific values for platform logs (uaa, haproxy or vcap);
    4. Set parsed_json_data_field_name to handle name of parsed json field. We store app parsed json to field named of @type (e.g. rtr, app etc.). And we store vcap message parsed json and app msg parsed json to field named of @source.component value;
    5. App parsing: store event_type to @type, source_type to @source.type.
    6. Rename parsed_json_data to parsed_json_field.
    7. Add field @index_type to store platform/app value.
    8. Update ES mappings and Kibana objects accordingly.
    Reconcile kibana configs with mappings and filters.
    
    * Use raw fields for visualization groups.
    * Replace @source.app.name with @source.app.
    * Use wildcard index patterns.

    Pull boshrelease into root of repo

    Add remaining dashboards
    Update UAA-Audit map
    Add UAA-Audit dashboard

    Extract named Kibana4 dashboard config into separate 'human readable' file, combine back into bulk insert request via bin/build

    Rework ES mappings (#242)
    
    * Rework mappings
    
    Add static mappings for parsed fields. Rework mappings. Use properties
    for app and platform index names. Fix some fields parsing
    (@shipper.priority).
    
    * Fix haproxy.* mappings, geoip.* mappings. Delete @cf.origin and *.cf_ignored_app fields (these fields have constant values).
    
    * Rename "APP/PROC/WEB" to just "APP" for simplicity.
    
    * Rework fields @source.index, .job_index and .vm
    
    App logs and platform logs from syslog release pass `job_index` field which is string bosh instance id. So we parse this field and store it as `@source.job_index`.
    Platform logs from metron agent pass `index` field which is numeric instance number. We store this field as `@source.index`. Additionally in this case, we set `@source.vm` field calculated as `job`/`index` (similar to how Logsearch sets it for Nats logs).
    
    Change parsing rules, tests and mappings accordingly.
    
    * Add mappings for new rtr fields
    
    * Update documentation for mappings
    Upload Kibana objects based on `firehose_events` property (#223)
    
    Kibana objects are moved from package to job to be loaded based on `firehose_events` deploy property.
    Rename kibana-dashboards to kibana-objects
    
    Actually we upload not only dashboards but also other Kibana objects
    (searches, visualizations, index patterns). So it's more convenient to
    name it 'objects' rather than 'dashboards'.
    Update Kibana searches, visualizations, dashboards
    
    1. Add/fix Kibana searches, visualizations, dashboards. Delete outdated stuff.
    2. Fix haproxy parsing by converting numeric fields ti int to make it possible use them in analytics.
    3. Update index_template mappings (add haproxy.request_verb.raw not_analyzed field to make it possible to use it in visualizations).
    Fields rework
    
    Make the same platform and app fields consistent, add useful fields.
    
    1. Sync. app basic fields (@source etc.) with platform fields (so that both indices have the same basic fields); Platform: set @source.origin field to 'system'/'cf'.
    2. Store app specific json cf_ fields to @cf;
    3. Set @type to specific values for platform logs (uaa, haproxy or vcap);
    4. Set parsed_json_data_field_name to handle name of parsed json field. We store app parsed json to field named of @type (e.g. rtr, app etc.). And we store vcap message parsed json and app msg parsed json to field named of @source.component value;
    5. App parsing: store event_type to @type, source_type to @source.type.
    6. Rename parsed_json_data to parsed_json_field.
    7. Add field @index_type to store platform/app value.
    8. Update ES mappings and Kibana objects accordingly.
    Reconcile kibana configs with mappings and filters.
    
    * Use raw fields for visualization groups.
    * Replace @source.app.name with @source.app.
    * Use wildcard index patterns.
    add app container metrics dashboards

    Rework ES mappings (#242)
    
    * Rework mappings
    
    Add static mappings for parsed fields. Rework mappings. Use properties
    for app and platform index names. Fix some fields parsing
    (@shipper.priority).
    
    * Fix haproxy.* mappings, geoip.* mappings. Delete @cf.origin and *.cf_ignored_app fields (these fields have constant values).
    
    * Rename "APP/PROC/WEB" to just "APP" for simplicity.
    
    * Rework fields @source.index, .job_index and .vm
    
    App logs and platform logs from syslog release pass `job_index` field which is string bosh instance id. So we parse this field and store it as `@source.job_index`.
    Platform logs from metron agent pass `index` field which is numeric instance number. We store this field as `@source.index`. Additionally in this case, we set `@source.vm` field calculated as `job`/`index` (similar to how Logsearch sets it for Nats logs).
    
    Change parsing rules, tests and mappings accordingly.
    
    * Add mappings for new rtr fields
    
    * Update documentation for mappings
    Get rid of HttpStart, HttpStop events processing
    
    Recently, dropsonde protocol removed HttpStart and HttpStop events,
    leaving HttpStartStop only (https://github.com/cloudfoundry/dropsonde-protocol/commit/3dd1473786cf6acdcc55e2206a58f08ad02f29ca). Even though current version of firehose-to-syslog is still uses these events processing, current versions of CloudFoundry don't operate these events, because they use latest dropsonde protocol. So we can get rid of these events in Logsearch-for-cloudfoundry to simplify processing.
    Upload Kibana objects based on `firehose_events` property (#223)
    
    Kibana objects are moved from package to job to be loaded based on `firehose_events` deploy property.
    Add mapping for logmessage.cf_ignored_app field
    
    New field cf_ignored_app was added to firehose-tosyslog. Add mapping for it.
    Rename `@source.instance` to `@source.job_index` (string guid), cease @source.name field
    
    https://github.com/cloudfoundry-community/logsearch-for-cloudfoundry/issues/217 (a change for job_index)
    Because `Index` field passed from Loggregator (doppler) was changed from uint instance number to guid instance ID, and firefox-to-syslog renamed `index` to `job_index`, the following changes were done in parsing:
    1. `@source.instance` renamed to `@source.job_index`. It's datatype changed from int to string - so no more converting to int is necessary.
    2. Because `source.job_index` is no more a short index of a job instance, but its bosh ID, we cease `@source.name` field (calculated as job+index before).
    3. Update Uindices and Kibana saved objects accordingly. Update UTs.
    Change UAA parsing to parse all UAA events
    
    We used to parse only UAA Audit events before. Change parsing rules to 1) parse UAA log using general format of UAA events 2) Additionaly parse Audit events using their specific message format.
    Update tests accordingly.
    
    Change Kibana objects for UAA to UAA Audit.
    Rename kibana-dashboards to kibana-objects
    
    Actually we upload not only dashboards but also other Kibana objects
    (searches, visualizations, index patterns). So it's more convenient to
    name it 'objects' rather than 'dashboards'.
    Kibana index-pattern upload
    
    1. Fix kibana4-dashboards.json.erb to upload Kibana index-patterns by id retrieved from json."title" instead of file name.
    2. Add logs-* index-paatern.
    3. Update fields of logs-app-* index pattern.
    4. Add Kibana config for Kibana version used in logsearch-boshrelease (4.4.0).

    Fields rework
    
    1. Remove _logstash_input field (we don't need it because we have @input field containing value of log input)
    2. Do not rename tags to @tags. This is incorrect to rename tags because logsearch-boshrelease also sets some tags after logsearch-for-cloudfoundry filters processed.

    Because `Index` field passed from Loggregator (doppler) was changed from uint instance number to guid instance ID, and firefox-to-syslog renamed `index` to `job_index`, the following changes were done in parsing:
    1. `@source.instance` renamed to `@source.job_index`. It's datatype changed from int to string - so no more converting to int is necessary.
    2. Because `source.job_index` is no more a short index of a job instance, but its bosh ID, we cease `@source.name` field (calculated as job+index before).
    3. Update Uindices and Kibana saved objects accordingly. Update UTs.
    Change UAA parsing to parse all UAA events
    
    We used to parse only UAA Audit events before. Change parsing rules to 1) parse UAA log using general format of UAA events 2) Additionaly parse Audit events using their specific message format.
    Update tests accordingly.
    
    Change Kibana objects for UAA to UAA Audit.
    Rename kibana-dashboards to kibana-objects
    
    Actually we upload not only dashboards but also other Kibana objects
    (searches, visualizations, index patterns). So it's more convenient to
    name it 'objects' rather than 'dashboards'.
    Update Kibana searches, visualizations, dashboards
    
    1. Add/fix Kibana searches, visualizations, dashboards. Delete outdated stuff.
    2. Fix haproxy parsing by converting numeric fields ti int to make it possible use them in analytics.
    3. Update index_template mappings (add haproxy.request_verb.raw not_analyzed field to make it possible to use it in visualizations).
    Kibana index-pattern upload
    
    1. Fix kibana4-dashboards.json.erb to upload Kibana index-patterns by id retrieved from json."title" instead of file name.
    2. Add logs-* index-paatern.
    3. Update fields of logs-app-* index pattern.
    4. Add Kibana config for Kibana version used in logsearch-boshrelease (4.4.0).
    Fields rework
    
    1. Remove _logstash_input field (we don't need it because we have @input field containing value of log input)
    2. Do not rename tags to @tags. This is incorrect to rename tags because logsearch-boshrelease also sets some tags after logsearch-for-cloudfoundry filters processed.
    3. Simplified if checks in snippets
    4. Reworked @type field
    5. Get rid of unparsed index (default index is platform)
    6. Update tests
    Fix incorrect file names (* is not allowed on Windows)
    Reconcile kibana configs with mappings and filters.
    
    * Use raw fields for visualization groups.
    * Replace @source.app.name with @source.app.
    * Use wildcard index patterns.

    * Rework mappings
    
    Add static mappings for parsed fields. Rework mappings. Use properties
    for app and platform index names. Fix some fields parsing
    (@shipper.priority).
    
    * Fix haproxy.* mappings, geoip.* mappings. Delete @cf.origin and *.cf_ignored_app fields (these fields have constant values).
    
    * Rename "APP/PROC/WEB" to just "APP" for simplicity.
    
    * Rework fields @source.index, .job_index and .vm
    
    App logs and platform logs from syslog release pass `job_index` field which is string bosh instance id. So we parse this field and store it as `@source.job_index`.
    Platform logs from metron agent pass `index` field which is numeric instance number. We store this field as `@source.index`. Additionally in this case, we set `@source.vm` field calculated as `job`/`index` (similar to how Logsearch sets it for Nats logs).

    Fields rework
    
    Make the same platform and app fields consistent, add useful fields.
    
    1. Sync. app basic fields (@source etc.) with platform fields (so that both indices have the same basic fields); Platform: set @source.origin field to 'system'/'cf'.
    2. Store app specific json cf_ fields to @cf;
    3. Set @type to specific values for platform logs (uaa, haproxy or vcap);
    4. Set parsed_json_data_field_name to handle name of parsed json field. We store app parsed json to field named of @type (e.g. rtr, app etc.). And we store vcap message parsed json and app msg parsed json to field named of @source.component value;
    5. App parsing: store event_type to @type, source_type to @source.type.
    6. Rename parsed_json_data to parsed_json_field.
    7. Add field @index_type to store platform/app value.
    8. Update ES mappings and Kibana objects accordingly.

    package authentication plugin for kibana
    
    [#112138459]
    
    Signed-off-by: Bence Monus <bence@cloudcredo.com>
    Ensure that all system certificates are trusted
    
    The Kibana auth plugin does not currently trust system certificates by default. When `kibana-auth.cloudfoundry.skip_ssl_validation` is false, the Kibana auth plugin fails to load and Kibana ignores failed plugins and then continues to load without authentication! The Kibana stderr logs indicate that the plugin fails to load due to a certificate error:
    
    ```
    ==> /var/vcap/sys/log/kibana/kibana.stderr.log <==
    config.ERROR fetching CF info from "https://<SYSTEM_DOMAIN>/v2/info { Error: unable to get local issuer certificate
        at TLSSocket.onConnectSecure (_tls_wrap.js:1058:34)
        at TLSSocket.emit (events.js:198:13)
        at TLSSocket._finishInit (_tls_wrap.js:636:8) code: 'UNABLE_TO_GET_ISSUER_CERT_LOCALLY' }
    ```
    
    This fix sets NODE_EXTRA_CA_CERTS to the system certificate bundle for Ubuntu if this file exists, which allows the Kibana auth plugin to load successfully, and therefore enabling authentication for Kibana.
    
    We have tested this script by manually editing config.sh on a running instance and verifying that it fixes the issue.

    Drop unused ingestor settings. (#235)
    
    * Drop unused port variable
    * Make doppler override optional
    Get rid of HttpStart, HttpStop events processing
    
    Recently, dropsonde protocol removed HttpStart and HttpStop events,
    leaving HttpStartStop only (https://github.com/cloudfoundry/dropsonde-protocol/commit/3dd1473786cf6acdcc55e2206a58f08ad02f29ca). Even though current version of firehose-to-syslog is still uses these events processing, current versions of CloudFoundry don't operate these events, because they use latest dropsonde protocol. So we can get rid of these events in Logsearch-for-cloudfoundry to simplify processing.

    Add custom filters option (#255)
    
    Allow passing new logstash filters directly from the new
    logstash_parser.custom_filters property. The whole string
    is written to file
    /var/vcap/jobs/logsearch-for-cloudfoundry-filters/config/logstash-filters-custom.conf
    
    The path must be loaded via property logstash_parser.filters similarly to
    how logstash-filters-default.conf is loaded in
    https://github.com/cloudfoundry-community/logsearch-for-cloudfoundry/blob/develop/docs/customization.md#parsing-rules
    
    The customization doc has been updated to describe the new property.
    Split packages (#221)
    
    * Split logsearch-for-cloudfoundry-filters job
    
    Instead of one job (and one package) logserach-for-cloudfoundry-filters,
    which actually included also es-mappings and kibana-saved-objects, we now
    split it and have three separate jobs (and packages accordingly):
    logsearch-config-logstash-filters, logserach-config-es-mappings and
    logsearch-config-kibana-objects.
    
    * Revert custom settings in template
    Add deployment dictionary lookup template
    
    Provide deployment dictionary lookup template for CF deployments (both cf and cf-diego). Names of deployments are configurable (logstash_parser.deployment_name.* properties).
    Set logstash_parser.deployment_dictionary property to path of this dictionary file (job parser) to make logsearch-boshrelease use it to override default dictionary (which contains logsearch deployment only).

    Add custom filters option (#255)
    
    Allow passing new logstash filters directly from the new
    logstash_parser.custom_filters property. The whole string
    is written to file
    /var/vcap/jobs/logsearch-for-cloudfoundry-filters/config/logstash-filters-custom.conf
    
    The path must be loaded via property logstash_parser.filters similarly to
    how logstash-filters-default.conf is loaded in
    https://github.com/cloudfoundry-community/logsearch-for-cloudfoundry/blob/develop/docs/customization.md#parsing-rules
    
    The customization doc has been updated to describe the new property.

    Consume system and apps domain from cloud_controller link
    UAA Redirects to Kibana on wrong domain (#270)
    
    The cf-kibana job's manifest.yml uses the CF apps domain for the Kibana app (i.e. logs.apps.cf.com) rather than the system domain.   But this UAA redirect assumes the Kibana app is available from the system domain.    This means UAA redirects will fail.
    
    It's possible that the alternative behavior would be to push the Kibana CF app to a route on the system domain itself rather than the apps domain (which should be a private domain owned by the CF system org).   That's how we worked around this in our install.

    Add "redirect" parameter when calling UAA /logout.do during Kibana logout.
    
    Redirect to Kibana /login after logout. Implemented using "redirect" parameter of UAA "/logout.do" endpoint. NOTE, that to work normally, redirects after logout should be enabled in UAA - https://github.com/cloudfoundry/uaa/blob/3.9.3/uaa/src/main/resources/login.yml#L38-L45.
